API Design Conventions – Locked Specification

Scope

This document locks the API design conventions for:
	•	Merchant Admin (React SPA) ↔ Java
	•	Public Site (Astro) ↔ Java
	•	Webhooks ↔ Java

Goals:
	•	Prevent churn
	•	Keep multi-tenant routing explicit and safe
	•	Standardize error handling, pagination, filtering, and sorting

⸻

1) URL Patterns & Versioning (Locked)

1.1 Base paths
	•	Internal (Merchant Admin / authenticated): /api/v1/...
	•	Public (Astro storefront / unauthenticated): /api/public/v1/...
	•	Webhooks: /api/webhooks/... (versioning optional; default unversioned unless a breaking change is expected)

1.2 Versioning strategy
	•	URL versioning is used (e.g., /v1).
	•	Any breaking change requires /v2.

1.3 Resource path conventions
	•	Nouns, plural resources: /products, /categories, /orders.
	•	Use nested resources for tenant scoping.

⸻

2) Tenant Resolution & Scoping (Locked)

2.1 Merchant Admin APIs (authenticated)
	•	Standard path includes tenant:
	•	/api/v1/tenants/{tenantId}/...
	•	Token is tenant-scoped and includes tenantId.
	•	Hard rule: pathTenantId == tokenTenantId enforced by centralized policy.

2.2 Public APIs (Astro)

Two supported resolution modes:
	1.	Primary (production): Host-based resolution

	•	Tenant resolved from the HTTP Host header (supports custom domains).
	•	Public endpoints are typically:
	•	/api/public/v1/catalog/...

	2.	Fallback (development / diagnostics): tenantSlug in path

	•	/api/public/v1/tenants/{tenantSlug}/catalog/...

Both are supported; Host-based is the default.

⸻

3) ID Formats (Locked)
	•	All entity IDs are UUIDs (tenants, users, products, categories, orders, payments, etc.).
	•	Human-friendly identifiers are separate fields, not primary keys:
	•	order_number (per-tenant sequence)
	•	future: booking_number

⸻

4) Error Format (Locked)

4.1 Standard error structure (RFC7807-like)

All non-2xx responses return a consistent structure:

{
  "type": "https://yourdomain.com/problems/validation-error",
  "title": "Validation error",
  "status": 400,
  "detail": "One or more fields are invalid.",
  "instance": "/api/v1/tenants/.../products",
  "traceId": "req-...",
  "errors": [
    { "field": "slug", "message": "Slug already exists." }
  ]
}

4.2 traceId
	•	traceId is included on all error responses.
	•	Recommended: include traceId on success responses as a header (e.g., X-Trace-Id).

4.3 Validation errors
	•	Always include errors[] with field-level messages where applicable.

⸻

5) Pagination (Locked)

5.1 Pagination type
	•	Use offset pagination for MVP.

5.2 Request parameters
	•	page (1-based)
	•	pageSize

Defaults:
	•	pageSize=20
	•	max pageSize=100

5.3 Response envelope

List endpoints return:

{
  "data": [ ... ],
  "page": 1,
  "pageSize": 20,
  "total": 182
}

Single-entity endpoints return the object directly (no data wrapper).

⸻

6) Filtering & Sorting (Locked)

6.1 Filtering
	•	Use query parameters.
	•	Common patterns:
	•	status=ACTIVE
	•	categoryId=<uuid>
	•	q=<searchTerm>

6.2 Search
	•	q is the standard parameter for search.

6.3 Sorting
	•	Use sort=field:direction
	•	Direction is asc or desc.
	•	Sorting fields must be allowlisted per endpoint.

Examples:
	•	?sort=createdAt:desc
	•	?sort=priceCents:asc

⸻

7) Payload & Data Formatting Conventions (Locked)

7.1 Enums
	•	Enums are returned as UPPER_SNAKE_CASE strings.

7.2 Timestamps
	•	All timestamps are ISO-8601 and UTC.
	•	Example: 2026-01-28T22:10:00Z

7.3 Money
	•	Money values use integer cents:
	•	priceCents, totalCents
	•	Currency uses ISO 4217:
	•	currency: "COP"

⸻

8) Success Response Conventions (Locked)
	•	Create endpoints typically return the created resource.
	•	Update endpoints return the updated resource.
	•	Delete endpoints return { "ok": true } or set a soft-delete/archived flag and return the resource.

⸻

9) Authentication Conventions (Locked)

9.1 Admin APIs
	•	Require Authorization: Bearer <accessToken>
	•	Access token TTL: 15 minutes
	•	Refresh token rotation: enabled (14-hour refresh TTL)

9.2 Public APIs
	•	No auth required by default.
	•	Rate limiting recommended (especially for search endpoints).

⸻

10) Webhook Conventions (Locked)
	•	Webhook endpoints live under /api/webhooks/...
	•	Webhooks must be idempotent.
	•	Webhook processing should record:
	•	provider event ID (if available)
	•	raw payload (optional)
	•	processing outcome

⸻

11) Final Locked Summary
	•	Admin base: /api/v1/...
	•	Public base: /api/public/v1/...
	•	Versioning via URL (/v1)
	•	Admin tenant scoping via path + token; enforced equality
	•	Public tenant resolution via Host, with tenantSlug fallback
	•	UUID IDs everywhere; human sequences as separate fields
	•	RFC7807-like error shape + traceId
	•	Offset pagination page/pageSize/total (20 default, 100 max)
	•	Filtering via query params; q for search
	•	Sorting via sort=field:dir allowlisted
	•	Enums UPPER_SNAKE_CASE; timestamps ISO-8601 UTC

This specification is locked and implementation-ready.